refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
public voidDs\Seq::rotate introtations
Rotates the seq by a given number of rotations, which is equivalent to successively calling $seq->push($seq->shift()) if the number of rotations is positive, or $seq->unshift($seq->pop()) if negative.

&reftitle.parameters;


  rotations



      The number of times the seq should be rotated.

&reftitle.examples;
Ds\Seq::rotate example
<?php $seq = new \Ds\Seq(["a", "b", "c", "d"]);
$seq->rotate(1); // "a" is shifted, then pushed. print_r($seq);
$seq->rotate(2); // "b" and "c" are shifted, then pushed. print_r($seq); ?>
&example.outputs.similar;
Ds\Seq Object ( [0] => b [1] => c [2] => d [3] => a ) Ds\Seq Object ( [0] => d [1] => a [2] => b [3] => c )
